At least 30 people, including drivers &amp;passengers, have been killed in the dispute linked to taxi routes between Mthatha &amp; Libode. CAPE TOWN Eastern Cape police are continuing a crackdown on taxis in the OR Tambo region amid on-going violence in which several people have lost their lives.At least 30 people, including drivers and passengers, have been killed in the disput linked to taxi routes between Mthatha and Libode.Seven people were arrested in operations this week, for murder and attempted murder, related to a deadly shooting which occurred in Ngqeleni last week.Eastern Cape police spokesperson Miranda Mills said, The provincial commissioner has commended the police for swift arrests and we will continue with our investigations. Transport MEC Weziwe Tikana says the violence is concerning and they seek to address the initial cause.